Reasoning: The paper deals with nonparametric estimation of characteristics for time series, which involves information theory and machine learning techniques. The use of archivers (or data compressors) as a tool for solving the problems suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of universal codes, which are commonly used in machine learning and data compression, indicating that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The problems of regression and classification suggest that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories, respectively. Finally, the use of practical methods of data compression in experimental results suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
